The practice laboratory consists of eight workstations, each one equipped with physical systems, such as a QUBE2 servo, a generator and a process simulator; with data acquisition equipments, such as PCIe cards, USB cards and programmable logic controllers; with instrumentation, such as power supplies and signal generators; and also with a UR3e collaborative robot.

The laboratory is used for real-time control practices of subjects such as Computer Control; programming of automatisms in Advanced Control Systems, as well as robot programming practices. 

Throughout the academic year, practical sessions are scheduled for a maximum of 16 students, with 2 students per workstation.
